According to the Risk Analysis Division (Risk Analysis Division) of the Capital Policy, the activity of the Hungarian Guard, constituted in August this year with the support of the Better Hungary Movement, has increased from a number of points of view the political risk of Hungary and the region.
The company's "risk warning" is written: in relation to the activity of the Hungarian Guard, the greatest political risk is the fact that "with the aggravation of the ethnic tensions existing between the Gypsy and non-Gypsy population of Hungary, even in the short term, violent ethnic clashes may occur".
The main reason for this is that the Hungarian Guard's political strategy is probably the provocation of an event of this character - the representative of the research institute added.
They stated that all of this is due to one of the main faults of the protagonists of Hungarian political life: "the protagonists of public life handed over the public debate of the Roma problem to representatives of radical and extremist political groups, who were able to base their political strategy on the discrepancies between Gypsies and Hungarians."
This aggravates the problem, prevents normal dialogue, strengthens extremists and increases the likelihood of outbreak of violent conflicts - they estimate.
Moreover, according to the research institute, the activity of the National Guard, as a result of the great attention of the national and international media, "has significantly deteriorated the image of Hungary abroad, especially with regard to the stability and democratic development of the country".
